  <text xml:lang="sa-Latn-t-sa-Deva" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="v_1">
          <l>kalpātikrūrakālabhrukuṭikuṭilatākalpakalpāgramuṣṭiḥ <caesura/> krudhyatkālīkaṭākṣāṅkita iva kalayan kāntim ekāntakālīm |</l>
          <l>krīḍaty asyākrameṇa krakacakṛtikṛtī kumbhikumbhāgrakūṭa<caesura/>kroḍeṣūtkṛttakaṇṭhotthitarudhirakaṇākīrṇakoṇaḥ kṛpāṇaḥ || 1 ||</l> 
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>As if adorned by its crossguard, curved like the contracted brow of cruel Kāla at the end of time,</l>
<l rend="indent">it assumes an absolute black splendour, as though branded by a sidelong glance from a sulking Kālī.</l>
<l>Master at hacking straight down the middle of the crest between elephants’ temples,</l>
<l rend="indent">his sword — edge splattered with blood gushing from severed throats — plays.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="v_2">
                <l>khaṃ preṅkhadbhiḥ kharāṃśoḥ prakharakharaśikhāḥ khaṇḍayan svair mayūkhaiḥ
                <caesura/>
khelāsaṃkhyeṣu khañjīkṛtaraṇarasikaḥ<anchor xml:id="khañjīkṛtaraṇarasikaḥ"/> saṃmukhānāṃ khanitram |</l>
                <l>khyātaḥ saukhyasya khāniḥ khalu kamitṛjuṣāṃ khecarīṇām akharvaḥ
                    <caesura/>
khelaty utkhātakhaḍgapratiyuvasu khanatkāravān asya khaḍgaḥ || 2 || </l>
                </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>
Shattering the fierce rays of the sun with its own, sweeping the sky,
                </l>
                <l>
It emasculates the lovers of war in carnal battles, excavator of enemies.
                </l>
                <l>
Famed mine of bliss, vast enough for the khecarīs devoted to their lover,
                </l>
                <l>
his sword — drilling out his young rivals, swords unsheathed — plays.
                </l>
            </lg>
          </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="v_3" source="alignments/v_3.xml">
                <l>
gāḍhaṃ gātrasya guptigrahaṇam avagaṇayyāgrataḥ svargamārgaṃ
                <caesura/>
grasyatrasyagrahāgresarakaraguṇitodagrajāgradgabhastiḥ |
                </l>
                <l>
garvogragranthigotragrahilaripugaṇagrāsabhaṅgīgṛhīto
                <caesura/>
garjaty agresarāgryagrahagilanaguruḥ saṃgare maṇḍalāgraḥ || 3 ||
                </l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Complete concealment of the body; giving up the path of heaven before it,</l>
<l>its fierce, waking rays are intensified by those of the moon, in fear of being consumed.</l>
<l>As if swallowing the enemy host obsessed with high birth, the firm fetters of their pride,</l>
<l>the scimitar roars in battle, guru of devouring the greatest of planets.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>        
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="v_4">
<l> ghrāṇaṃ saṃgrāmalakṣmyā ghanasṛtiyaśasām aṅghrir udgho mahārgha<caesura/>syopaghnaḥ sāhasasyālaghuhṛdayalaghur bhītyaghaughasya vighnaḥ |</l>
<l>ghoṭaḥ kīrter ghanābhāpaghanagajaghaṭāghātanairghṛṇyanighno <caesura/>ghūrṇaty udgharmaghṛṣṭiprakaraghṛṇisamāghrātighoro 'sya khaḍgaḥ || 4 ||</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The scent of glory in battle ― the foot of those famed for uninterrupted movement ― the excellence of the great offering ―</l>
<l>support of violence, light but heavy-hearted — obstacle against the flood of fear and evil,</l>
<l>the horse of fame ― subservient to the cruelty of slashing through the temples of cloud-bodied elephants,</l>
<l>his sword swirls, terrible because of the smell of waves in a multitude of hot whirlpools.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
      <div n="5">
        <lg xml:id="v_5">
          <l>
caṇḍaś caṇḍīśacakṣuś cirabhṛtaviṣamārcidhvajāc cānubhāle
<caesura/>
caṇḍyāś cāmīkarābhe 'ñjanacayakhacitaṃ citrakaṃ kauryacañcuḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
citraṃ svācāntavīrāsur api ravirucā cumbitaś cākacikyāc
<caesura/>
cakṣuḥkarmāṇi cūṣaty acirarucirucāṃ vañcako 'syāsir uccaiḥ || 5 ||
        </l>
        </lg>
      </div>
      <div n="6">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_6">
          <l>
chāyāvāñchānurūpocchalitaripuśucau chādanaṃ kṛcchravṛṣṭau
<caesura/>
chāyāvāhāśanes tacchalasamitilasacchauryakālālipuccham |
          </l>
          <l>
chātacchāttripravīraḥ chiduragaṇacaṇaś chekahṛcchokakārī
<caesura/>
chāyākāntacchavīcchāvyatikaravaśato mūrcchatīddho 'sya khaḍgaḥ || 6 ||
        </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_6">
...vittaś chiduragaṇacaṇaḥ | "tena vittaḥ-" iti caṇap | chekānāṃ nāgarāṇāṃ hṛcchokakārī ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="7">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_7">
          <l>
jaṅghālo jaitrajanyājirabhuvi janayañ jantujāte jvarārtiṃ
<caesura/>
jīvātur bāhujasya trijagati jayino dorbhujaṅgasya jihvā |
          </l>
          <l>
jyājānir vyāgrajāgradgajaradanaśilābhañjanājasrayogyo
<caesura/>
jātajvālo jaṭāvān iha jayati jagajjitvaro 'muṣya khaḍgaḥ || 7 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_7">
jam iti || amuṣya khaḍga iha loke jayati | kiṃvidhaḥ | jaitraṃ jayaśīlaṃ yaj janyaṃ saṃgrāmas tasyājirabhuvi jaṅghālaḥ | satvara ity arthaḥ || "jaṅghālo 'tijave" ity amaraḥ | jantujāte prāṇimātre jvarārti jvarapīḍāṃ janayan | trijagati trailokye jayinaḥ parākramavato bāhujasya kṣattriyasya jīvātur jīvanauṣadham | "jīvātur jīvanauṣadham" ity amaraḥ | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | athavā trijagati jayino dorbhujaṅgasya bāhusarpasya jihvā | jyājānir vasudhājāniḥ || "jāyāyā niṅ" | "vasudhāmaurvyor jyā" iti medinī | vyāgrāś ca jāgradgajaradanāś ca śilāś ca tāsāṃ bhañjanaṃ tatrājasraṃ yogyaḥ | jātā jvālā yasmin sa tathā | ata eva jaṭāvān | jagajjitvaraḥ ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="8">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_8">
          <l>
jhātkārāñ jaitrajanye jhagiti janayato janmikarṇajvarārtiṃ
<caesura/>
jhañjhāvātānukārāñjhaṇajhaṇitijhaṇatkāriṇaḥ projjihānaḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
jhāṣāṅkīṃ tām avasthāṃ jhagiti ripujanaṃ grāhayan dhūrjaṭīṣṭāṃ
<caesura/>
jhūrannamrāhiteṣūjjhitaraṇarabhasaṃ projjihīte 'sya khaḍgaḥ || 8 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p n="8" xml:id="c_8">
jhād iti || asya khaḍga ujjhitaraṇarabhasaṃ saṃprās tādaraṃ yathātathā projjihīte gacchati | kiṃvidhaḥ | jaitrajanye jayaśīle saṃgrāme jhagiti jhātkārān anukaraṇaśabdān projjihānaḥ | kṛtavān ity arthaḥ | "ohāṅ gatau" | kiṃvidhāñ jhātkārān | jhañjhāvātānukārān suvṛṣṭikavātasadṛśān | punaḥ kiṃvidhān | jhaṇajhaṇitijhaṇatkāriṇaḥ | kiṃkurvan san | tāṃ prasiddhāṃ jhāṣāṅkīṃ mānmathīm avasthām | bhasmarūpām ity arthaḥ | ripujanaṃ vairilokaṃ jhagiti śīghraṃ grāhayan | kiṃvidhām avasthām | dhūrjaṭeḥ śaṃbhor iṣṭām | namrā ye 'hitās teṣu jhūraṃl lajjan |
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="9">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_9">
          <l>
ṭaṃkāroddhaṭṭitā yā jhaṭiti vighaṭayan koṭiśaś cāpayaṣṭīṣ 
<caesura/>
ṭaṅko vidviḍgirīṇāṃ karaṭikaṭakaṭāhātikuṭṭāgrakoṭiḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
duṣkūṭair yaṣṭikūṭaiḥ kuṭukuṭilasaṭaiḥ paṭṭiśaiḥ koṭisaṃkhyaiḥ
<caesura/>
kheṭair durghāṭavāṭān pratibhaṭasubhaṭāṃṣ ṭīkate 'muṣya khaḍgaḥ || 9 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_9">
ṭam iti || amuṣya khaḍgaḥ pratibhaṭasubhaṭān pratipakṣavīrān drāk śīghraṃ ṭīkate | tān prati gacchatīty arthaḥ | kiṃvidhaḥ | ṭaṃkāreṇa śabdenoddhaṭṭitāḥ prakaṭitāḥ yāḥ koṭiśo 'saṃkhyāś cāpayaṣṭīr jhaṭiti śīghraṃ vighaṭayan | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | vidviṣāṃ girayas teṣāṃ ṭaṅko vidārakaḥ | punaḥ | karaṭino gajās teṣāṃ kaṭā gaṇḍasthalāni ta eva kaṭāhās tailādipākapātrāṇi teṣāṃ kuṭṭā piṣṭīkaraṇasamarthāgrakoṭir yasyeti | kiṃvidhān pratibhaṭasubhaṭān | duṣkūṭair duṣṭāgrair yaṣṭikūṭair yaṣṭisamūhaiḥ kaṭukuṭilasaṭaiḥ paṭṭiśaiḥ khaḍgaiḥ phalakair durghāṭo vāṭo mārgo yeṣāṃ te | koṭisaṃkhyair iti viśeṣaṇaṃ triṣv api yojyam ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="10">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_10">
          <l>
ṭhātkārī kaṇṭhasīmany atikaṭhinatare skandhapīṭhe kaṭhore
<caesura/>
pṛṣṭhāṣṭhīlānukāre śaṭhakamaṭhapateḥ kumbhapṛṣṭhe 'pi caibhe |
          </l>
          <l>
drāgdrāghiṣṭhaḥ kaṭhoracchavijaraṭhataradyotasaṃghaṭṭamūrchat<caesura/>koṣṭhāḥ kāṣṭhāḥ prakurvan ripuśirasi luṭhaty etadīyaḥ kuṭhāraḥ || 10 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_10">
ṭhātkārīti || etadīyaḥ kuṭhāro ripuśirasi drāk śīghraṃ luṭhati | kiṃvidhaḥ | aibhe hastisaṃbandhini kaṇṭhasīmani kaṇṭhasamīpadeśe ṭhātkārī śabdakartā | kiṃvidhe kaṇṭhasīmani | atikaṭhinatare | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | kaṭhore skandhapīṭhe ṭhātkārī | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | aibhe kumbhapṛṣṭhe ṭhātkārī | kiṃvidhe kumbhapṛṣṭhe | śaṭhakamaṭhapater dhūrtakacchapasya | "śaṭho dhattūrake dhūrte madhyasthapuruṣe 'lase" iti mahīpaḥ | pṛṣṭhāṣṭhīlānukāre pṛṣṭhasyāṣṭhīlaṃ tattulye | drāghiṣṭho dīrghaḥ | kaṭhoracchaviḥ sūryas tasya jaraṭhataro yo dyotaḥ prakāśas tasya saṃghaṭṭas tena mūrchat dviguṇībhavan | "jakṣityādayaḥ ṣaṭ" iti num na | kiṃ kurvan san | kāṣṭhā diśaḥ koṣṭhāḥ svādhīnāḥ prakurvan san | "koṣṭhaḥ kusūle cātmīye madhye kukṣer gṛhasya ca" iti medinī ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="11">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_11">
          <l>
ḍimbho daṇḍāyudhasya pradhanaghanataḍiccaṇḍadoḥ kuṇḍalīndra<caesura/>kṣveḍaḥ proddaṇḍadarpadviradananigaḍo ḍiṇḍimaḥ śauryabhartuḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
asya prācaṇḍyabhāṇḍaṃ dhṛtamadhupagaladgaṇḍavetaṇḍaśuṇḍā<caesura/>kāṇḍaṃ khaṇḍaṃ vitanvan yudhi dhutajaḍimā hiṇḍate maṇḍalāgraḥ || 11 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_11">
ḍim iti || asya maṇḍalāgro hiṇḍata itas tato gacchati | kiṃvidhaḥ | daṇḍāydhasya yamasya ḍimbhaḥ śiśuḥ | ‘potaḥ pāko 'rbhako ḍimbhaḥ’ ity amaraḥ | pradhanam eva saṃgrāma eva ghanataḍit tasyāś caṇḍador hastaḥ kuṇḍalīndraḥ śeṣas tat kṣveḍo garalam | ‘kṣveḍas tu garalaṃ viṣam’ ity amaraḥ | proddaṇḍo darpo yeṣāṃ te ye dviradanā gajās teṣāṃ nigaḍo 'ndukaḥ | śauryabhartur ḍiṇḍimaḥ sūcakavādyaviśeṣaḥ | pracaṇḍasya bhāvas tathā, tadbhāṇḍam adhikaraṇam | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | yudhi saṃgrāme dhṛtā madhupā yais tair galantaḥ sravanto gaṇḍā yeṣāṃ te evaṃvidhā vetaṇḍā gajās teṣāṃ śuṇḍās tāsāṃ kāṇḍaṃ samūhaṃ khaṇḍaṃ chedaṃ vitanvan vistārayan | dhuto jaḍimā yena saḥ ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="12">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_12">
          <l>
ḍhakkāsvārūḍhakīrtiprasṛtisuvijayaśrīvivoḍhā nirūḍho 
<caesura/>
vāḍhaṃ soḍhātigāḍhapraharaṇasamitau līḍhakoṣṇāstrasīdhuḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
rīḍhā gūḍhaprahartur draḍhimakulagṛhaṃ nyastaśastreṣu ṣaṇḍho 
<caesura/>
nirvyūḍhodgāḍhayuddhapratihatiṣu dṛḍhaṃ ḍhaukate 'muṣya khaḍgaḥ || 12 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_12">
ḍheti || amuṣya khaḍgo nirvyūḍhodgāḍhayuddhā vīrās teṣāṃ pratihatayo vraṇās tāsu dṛḍhaṃ ḍhaukate pravartate | kiṃvidhaḥ | ḍhakkayā vijayamardalena suṣṭu ārūḍhā yā kīrtis tasyāḥ prasṛtiḥ prasaras tasyāṃ suvijayaśrīs tasyā vivoḍhā | nirūḍhaḥ khyātaḥ | atigāḍhapraharaṇā yā samitiḥ saṃgrāmas tatra vāḍhaṃ soḍhā sahanaśīlaḥ | punaḥ kiṃvidhaḥ | līḍham āsvāditaṃ koṣṇaṃ kiṃcid uṣṇaṃ yad astraṃ tad eva sīdhur madyaṃ yena | gūḍhaprahartur aprakaṭamāraṇakartū rīḍhāvamānanā | draḍhimnaḥ kulagṛhaṃ dṛḍhatāyā adhiṣṭhānam | nyastaśastreṣu tyaktāyudheṣu ṣaṇḍho niḥsāraḥ ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="13">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_13">
          <l>
prāṇā darpasya pāṇī raṇaśamanaśiśoḥ kārmaṇaṃ dveṣaṇānāṃ
<caesura/>
tūrṇaṃ sadvārabāṇavraṇakaraṇakṛtī kīrṇadurmarṣaṇārciḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
koṣṇadviṭśoṇitāktaḥ kharakiraṇaghṛṇiśreṇiśāṇo 'ruṇaśrīr
<caesura/>
udgūrṇo vāraṇānāṃ gaṇam asṛṇi śṛṇāty asya tīkṣṇaḥ kṛpāṇaḥ || 13 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_13">
prāṇā iti || asya tīkṣṇaḥ kṛpāṇo vāraṇānāṃ gajānāṃ gaṇaṃ samūham asṛṇi sṛṇirahitaṃ yathātathā śṛṇāti | śṝ hiṃsāyām | mārayatīty arthaḥ | kiṃvidhaḥ darpasya balasya prāṇāḥ | bahutvena nirdeśaḥ | raṇa eva śamanaśiśus tasya pāṇir hastaḥ | pāṇī raṇeti ‘ro rī’ iti ‘ḍhralope’ iti dīrghaḥ | dveṣaṇānāṃ śatrūṇām | ‘dviṣaddveṣaṇadurhṛdaḥ’ ity amaraḥ | kārmaṇaṃ mūlakarma | tūrṇaṃ śīghraṃ sad yad vārabāṇaṃ kavacaṃ | ‘kañcuko 'strīvārabāṇaḥ’ ity amaraḥ | tatra vraṇakaraṇaṃ tatra kuśalaḥ | kīrṇaṃ prasāritaṃ durmarṣaṇaṃ duḥsaham arcir yena | koṣṇaṃ yad dviṣatāṃ śoṇitaṃ raktaṃ tenāktaḥ siktaḥ | kharakiraṇaḥ śrīsūryas tasya ghṛṇayo mayūkhās teṣāṃ śreṇis tasyāḥ śāṇo gharṣanapāṣāṇaḥ | aruṇā śrīr yasya saḥ | udgūrṇa utthāpitaḥ || 
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="14">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_14">
          <l>
tṛpyaddantikṣitīndraṃ taralatarataratpattibhaṅgaṃ vighūrṇat<caesura/>tuṅgāśvāvartagartaṃ niśitatamamilatkuntasaṃtānacakram |
          </l>
          <l>
tvaṅgattīkṣṇāsitūrvattimim anatidalacchaktiśuktiṃ raṇābdhiṃ 
<caesura/>
tāras tūrṇaṃ titīrṣus tṛṇalavavad arīn asya khaḍgas tṛṇeḍhi || 14 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_14">
tṛpyad iti || asya khaḍgo 'rīñ śatrūṃs tṛnalavavat tṛṇeḍhi | mārayatīty arthaḥ | ‘tṛha hiṃsāyām’ | kiṃvidhaḥ | tūrṇaṃ śīghraṃ raṇābdhiṃ saṃgrāmasamudraṃ titīrṣus taraṇecchuḥ | ‘tṝ plavanataraṇayoḥ’ | tāra ujjvalaḥ | kiṃvidhaḥ raṇābdhiṃ | tṛpyanto dantina eva kṣitīndrāḥ parvato yasmiṃs tathā tam | taralatarā aticañcalās taranto ye pattayaḥ padātayas ta eva bhaṅgās taraṅgā yasmiṃs tam | vighūrṇantas tuṅgā ye 'śvās ta evāvartagartā yasmiṃs tam | … … … … | tvaṅgantas tīkṣṇā ye 'sayas ta eva tūrvattimayo yasminn iti tathā tam | anatidalacchaktaya eva śuktayo yasmiṃs tam ||     
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="15">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_15">
          <l>
sthūlaṃ sthūlaṃ śvasadbhiḥ prathitapṛthupṛṣadvīkṣaṇais tīrthamātraṃ
<caesura/>
saṃmanvānair apārthaṃ śithilaraṇakathair vepathuvyarthaśastraiḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
saṃprāptaiḥ sthāṇusaṃsthāṃ prathitapathacarais trastanetrātithitvaṃ
<caesura/>
nītaḥ pratyarthisārthair vyathayati savidhasthān apīddho 'sya khaḍgaḥ || 15 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_15">
sthūlam iti || asyeddhaḥ samṛddhaḥ khaḍgaḥ savidhasthān api samīpavartino 'pi vyathayati | kiṃvidhaḥ | pratyarthisārthaiḥ paripanthisamūhais trastāni yāni netrāṇi tatrātithitvaṃ nītaḥ | dṛṣṭa iti yāvat | kiṃvidhaiḥ pratyarthisārthaiḥ | sthūlaṃ sthūlaṃ dīrghaṃ dīrghaṃ śvasadbhiḥ | asahyatvāt | prathitapṛthu pṛṣanto bindavas tadyuktāni vīkṣaṇāni yeṣāṃ taiḥ | tīrthamātraṃ saṃmanvānaiḥ | apārthaṃ nirarthakaṃ śithilā raṇakathā yeṣāṃ te tathā taiḥ | vepathunā kampena vyarthāni śastrāṇi yeṣāṃ te taiḥ | ata eva sthāṇusaṃsthāṃ saṃprāptaiḥ | prathito yaḥ panthās tatra carantīti carās taiḥ | mahāpathas tu maraṇam iti ||    
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="16">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_16">
          <l>
dṛpyaddoḥkālakūṭadrumataruṇadalaṃ darpadantāvalendra<caesura/>drāghīyodānalekhā daradalitadalendīvaradroṇidehaḥ |
          </l>
          <l>
dīvyannaidāghamadhyaṃdinadivasamaṇidyotaduṣprekṣyadīptir
<caesura/>
dauḥsthityaṃ dīrghadīrghaṃ dadad arisudṛśāṃ dīpyate 'muṣya khaḍgaḥ || 16 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_16"><hi>dṛpyad</hi> iti || <hi>amuṣya khaḍgo dīvyate</hi><note place="foot">The commentator seems to have a different reading from the verse.</note> krīḍate | kiṃvidhaḥ | <hi>dṛpyad</hi> yad <hi>dor</hi> bāhuḥ sa eva <hi>kālakūṭadrumo</hi> viṣatarus tasya <hi>taruṇadalaṃ</hi> navīnapatram | <hi>darpadantāvalendro</hi> hastīndras tasya <hi>drāghīyo</hi> dīrghā <hi>dānalekhā</hi> | <hi>daram</hi> īṣad <hi>dalitaṃ</hi> viśīrṇaṃ <hi>dalaṃ</hi> yasyaivaṃvidham <hi>indīvaraṃ</hi> tasya <hi>droṇir</hi> madhyabhāgas tadvad <hi>deho</hi> yasya sa tathā | śyāma iti yāvat | <hi>dīvyad</hi> yan <hi>naidāghamadhyaṃdinam</hi> uṣṇakālamadhyāhnaṃ tatra yo <hi>divasamaṇis</hi> tasya <hi>dyotaḥ</hi> prakāśas tena <hi>duṣprekṣyā</hi> <hi>dīptir</hi> yasya saḥ | <hi>arisudṛśāṃ</hi> vairistrīṇāṃ <hi>dīrghadīrgham</hi> atimahad <hi>dauḥsthyaṃ</hi> duḥsthasya bhāvas tathā tad <hi>dadat</hi> ||
        </p>
      </div>
      <div n="17">
        <lg type="verse" xml:id="v_17">
          <l>
dhairyasyādhārayaṣṭir dhṛtaviṣudhavadhūsādhvaso dhāma dhāmnāṃ
<caesura/>
dhūmaḥ krodhānalasya pradhanarathavarasyoddhuro dhūrdharo 'yam |
          </l>
          <l>
dhīrodāttor dhvavāhā dharaṇidharadhṛtas tīkṣṇadhārādharo 'ddhā
<caesura/>
dhīrān auddhatyabhājo raṇadharaṇicarānasya dhūnoti khaḍgaḥ || 17 ||
          </l>
        </lg>
        <p xml:id="c_17">
dhairyasyeti || asyāyaṃ khaḍga auddhatyabhājo raṇadharaṇicarān saṃgrāmabhūmigatān dhīrān dhūnoti kampayati | kiṃvidhaḥ | dhairyasya guṇasyādhārayaṣṭiḥ | dhṛtaṃ viṣudhavadhūnāṃ devastrīṇāṃ sādhvasaṃ yena saḥ | dhāmnāṃ tejasāṃ dhāmādhiṣṭhānam | krodha evānalas tasya dhūmaḥ | pradhanaṃ saṃgrāmas tad eva rathavaras tasyoddhuro dhūrdharo bhāradhartā | dhīrodāttaḥ puruṣaśreṣṭhas tasyordhvavāhā hastaḥ | ‘bhujā vāhā’ iti strītvena nirdeśaḥ | dhīrodāttalakṣaṇaṃ rasakalikāyām ― ‘caturdhā puruṣaḥ ― dhīrodātto dhīralalito dhīraśānto dhīroddhataś ceti | tatra ― kṛpāvān atigambhīro vinītaś cāvikatthanaḥ | dhīrodāttaḥ sa vijñeyo rāmo dāśarathir yathā ||’ iti | dharaṇidhareṇa rājñā dhṛtaḥ | tīkṣṇadhārādharaḥ | ‘addhā’ ity aṅgīkāro 'vyayam ||
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
